{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Steel|type2=Ghost}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Steel|prevnum=678|prev=Meowstic|nextnum=680|next=Doublade}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Honedge\n|jname=ヒトツキ\n|tmname=Hitotsuki\n|category=Sword\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Steel\n|type2=Ghost\n|abilityn=1\n|abilitylayout=1\n|ability1=No Guard\n|ndex=679\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=117\n|height-ftin=2\'07"\n|height-m=0.8\n|weight-lbs=4.4\n|weight-kg=2.0\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Mineral\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|expyield=65\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=180\n|body=05\n|pokefordex=honedge\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Honedge\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ヒトツキ\'\'\' \'\'Hitotsuki\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Steel|Ghost}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Doublade}} starting at [[level]] 35, which evolves into {{p|Aegislash}} when exposed to a [[Dusk Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:XY Prerelease Honedge unsheathed.png|thumb|left|150px|Honedge with its sheath removed]]\nHonedge is a Pokémon that resembles a sword from the medieval times. Its body is a silver sword with a light gray hilt. Embedded in the hilt is a blue gem with a dark center that appears to be its eye. Attached to the pommel is a long, dark blue cloth with a swirl design in lighter blue at the tip; the tip of the sash splits into four tassels. The sash is known to suck the life energy out of anyone who dares to grab it by the hilt. Honedge\'s sheath is dark brown with curved lines resembling a {{wp|triquetra}} across its surface. Near the top of the sheath are white teeth-like markings and rings with white centers that resemble eyes. A third ring extends onto the hilt and encircles its actual eye.\n{{left clear}}\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Sawyer Honedge.png|thumb|left|250px|Honedge in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\nHonedge debuted in \'\'[[Diancie — Princess of the Diamond Domain]]\'\'. The same Honedge, under the ownership of [[Argus Steel]], reappeared in \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\'.\n\nA Honedge appeared in \'\'[[XY106|A Meeting of Two Journeys!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Sawyer]]. It was used in his {{pkmn|battle}} against {{Ash}}, but was defeated by {{AP|Pikachu}}. It [[Evolution|evolved]] into Doublade sometime before \'\'[[XY119|A Full-Strength Battle Surprise!]]\'\', and it evolved again into Aegislash sometime before \'\'[[XY126|Valuable Experience for All!]]\'\'.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nHonedge made its main series debut in \'\'[[XY080|Performing with Fiery Charm!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Performer}}. She used it during the Rookie Class [[Pokémon Showcase]] in [[Dendemille Town]]. It appeared again in \'\'[[XY112|Master Class is in Session!]]\'\', being used by its {{pkmn|Trainer}} in the Master Class Showcase in [[Gloire City]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY106|Honedge|Ash\'s Pokédex|Honedge, the Sword Pokémon. It is said that Honedge is actually a spirit living inside a sword.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Honedge Lunatone Gyarados Talonflame Salamence PG.png|thumb|250px|Honedge in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\nTwo soldiers\' Honedge appeared in \'\'[[PG18|The Redemption]]\'\', during a fantasy of a story from the past. They were some of the many Pokémon fighting in the great war of [[Kalos]] 3,000 years previously.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Celosia Honedge Adventures.png|thumb|230px|Honedge in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[Celosia]] of [[Team Flare]] owns a Honedge, which she used in conjunction with her {{p|Aegislash}} to possess {{adv|Shauna}}. It first appeared in \'\'[[PAXY05|Kangaskhan...Kangascan\'t]]\'\'.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Honedge (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS/Wii U|Super Smash Bros. for Wii U]]===\nHonedge makes a cameo appearance in the {{st|Kalos Pokémon League}} stage. When the stage transitions to the {{DL|Pokémon League (Kalos)|Ironworks Chamber}}, it can be seen in the background along with {{p|Steelix}}, {{p|Scizor}}, and {{p|Klinklang}}.\n\n====Trophy information====\n\'\'\'NA:\'\'\' \'\'The origin of this Pokémon is a great ghost tale: it\'s said that Honedge are ancient swords possessed by a departed spirit. Should people try to grab the sword, Honedge will attack them or wrap its sash around their arm, slowly draining the life energy from their body. Moral of the story: be careful around ancient swords.\'\'\n\n\'\'\'PAL:\'\'\' \'\'There\'s a rather spooky tale behind this Pokémon\'s origins: apparently, it\'s an ancient sword possessed by a departed spirit. Honedge won\'t let anyone grip its hilt. If they try, it will attack them or wrap its sash around their arm and drain the life energy from their body! Yikes!\'\'\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=steel|type2=ghost}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=117|label1=Central|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person\'s arm and drains that person\'s life energy completely.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person\'s arm and drains that person\'s life energy completely.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\