he ones to attack humans. Considering it drains the life of those who wield it, it may have also been based on the cursed {{wp|tyrfing}}. Visually, considering its build and hilt, Honedge seems to be based on either a {{wp|spatha}}, {{wp|claymore}}, or possibly {{wp|jian}} sword, with its own {{wp|scabbard}} and {{wp|Hilt#Sword_knot|tassel}}-like prehensile limb. The design on both Honedge and Doublade\'s sheath resembles that of a {{wp|triquetra}}, clearly depicted on Honedge and more ornately designed on Doublade\'s.\n\n====Name origin====\nHonedge may be a combination of \'\'hone\'\', \'\'one\'\', and \'\'edge\'\'.\n\nHitotsuki may be a combination of 一つ \'\'hitotsu\'\' (one) and 突き \'\'tsuki\'\' (stab, lunge, or thrust) or 憑き \'\'tsuki\'\' ({{wp|spirit possession}}).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Steel|type2=Ghost\n|ja=ヒトツキ \'\'Hitotsuki\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|一つ \'\'hitotsu\'\'|one}} and {{tt|突き \'\'tsuki\'\'|stab, lung, or thrust}} or {{tt|憑き \'\'tsuki\'\'|spirit possession}}\n|fr=Monorpale|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|mono|one}}\'\', \'\'{{tt|empaler|impale}}\'\', and possibly \'\'{{wp|vorpal sword|vorpale}}\'\'\n|es=Honedge|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Gramokles|demeaning=From \'\'{{wp|Gram (mythology)|Gram}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|Damoklesschwert|Sword of Damocles}}\'\'\n|it=Honedge|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=단칼빙 \'\'Dankalbing\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|단 (單) \'\'dan\'\'|single}}, {{tt|칼 \'\'kal\'\'|sword, dagger}}, and {{tt|빙의 (憑依) \'\'bing-ui\'\'|spirit possession}}\n|zh_yue=獨劍鞘 \'\'Duhkgimchiu\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|獨 \'\'duhk\'\'|single}}, {{tt|劍 \'\'gim\'\'|sword}}, and {{tt|鞘 \'\'chiu\'\'|sheath}}\n|zh_cmn=獨劍鞘 \'\'Dújiànqiào\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|獨 \'\'dú\'\'|single}}, {{tt|劍 \'\'jiàn\'\'|sword}}, and {{tt|鞘 \'\'qiào\'\'|sheath}}\n|hi=हॉनएड्ज \'\'Honedge\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Хонедж \'\'Khonedzh\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External